Subject:Re: [child_lit] child_lit] middle school novels about hunger
	and	emotional hunger
Has anyone mentioned Esther Hautzig's 'The Endless Steppe',  which is about exiles in Siberia, and includes a lot about hunger and deprivation.

The hero of Anne Holm's 'I Am David' suffers from both literal and emotional hunger.

Elizabeth Laird's 'The Coldest Winter' deals with people living in 19th century Ireland at a time of famine.


Ann

